{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HvYpLZkrc5Dsr5z65fEs68","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature;\n     2→\n     3→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.CreateUserInput;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     5→\n     6→public interface CreateUser {\n     7→  User handle(CreateUserInput createUserInput);\n     8→}\n     9→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VWywaoMKfDQLjyVUhPbx8t","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"e7860d26-d274-4c47-8fc0-33353145e2f2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015UPRF8PVwamZ3EFkQTmQTB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.EmailAlreadyExistsException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UsernameAlreadyExistsException;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateUser;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.CreateUserInput;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    13→\n    14→@Singleton\n    15→public class CreateUserImpl implements CreateUser {\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private HashProvider hashProvider;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    23→\n    24→    @Override\n    25→    public User handle(CreateUserInput createUserInput) {\n    26→        final var user =\n    27→                userBuilder.build(\n    28→                        createUserInput.getUsername(),\n    29→                        createUserInput.getEmail(),\n    30→                        createUserInput.getPassword());\n    31→        checkExistingUsername(user.getUsername());\n    32→        checkExistingEmail(user.getEmail());\n    33→        user.setPassword(hashProvider.hashPassword(user.getPassword()));\n    34→        userRepository.save(user);\n    35→        return user;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    private void checkExistingUsername(String username) {\n    39→        if (userRepository.existsByUsername(username)) {\n    40→            throw new UsernameAlreadyExistsException();\n    41→        }\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    private void checkExistingEmail(String email) {\n    45→        if (userRepository.existsByEmail(email)) {\n    46→            throw new EmailAlreadyExistsException();\n    47→        }\n    48→    }\n    49→}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VWywaoMKfDQLjyVUhPbx8t","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"36719e18-f3e3-4ed9-8256-b5559abdc982"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Xn6DHV2HpK99d5Sw9HjWm3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature;\n     2→\n     3→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.LoginUserInput;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     5→\n     6→public interface LoginUser {\n     7→  User handle(LoginUserInput loginUserInput);\n     8→}\n     9→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VWywaoMKfDQLjyVUhPbx8t","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"c142d214-dd9e-4cb0-9158-023af2d552cd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01J9RZDoxzzLRWYu3PDg5cLF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.LoginUserInput;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    12→\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class LoginUserImpl implements LoginUser {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    private HashProvider hashProvider;\n    20→\n    21→    @Override\n    22→    public User handle(LoginUserInput loginUserInput) {\n    23→        final var user =\n    24→                userRepository\n    25→                        .findByEmail(loginUserInput.getEmail())\n    26→                        .orElseThrow(UserNotFoundException::new);\n    27→        if (!isPasswordValid(loginUserInput.getPassword(), user.getPassword())) {\n    28→            throw new InvalidPasswordException();\n    29→        }\n    30→        return user;\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    private boolean isPasswordValid(String password, String hashedPassword) {\n    34→        return hashProvider.checkPassword(password, hashedPassword);\n    35→    }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VWywaoMKfDQLjyVUhPbx8t","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"8f5c04de-f1ed-46e9-9ece-1af0d4fd51fb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WoYXUvVP4dBg7QbP9Djjuz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature;\n     2→\n     3→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UpdateUserInput;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     5→\n     6→public interface UpdateUser {\n     7→  User handle(UpdateUserInput updateUserInput);\n     8→}\n     9→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VWywaoMKfDQLjyVUhPbx8t","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"100d7544-8fc9-4e08-9e2b-0f5d3b988d34"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YXB1xDqGrfmrNhAP8fM9XR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.EmailAlreadyExistsException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UsernameAlreadyExistsException;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UpdateUser;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UpdateUserInput;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.UUID;\n    15→\n    16→@Dependent\n    17→public class UpdateUserImpl implements UpdateUser {\n    18→\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    25→\n    26→    @Override\n    27→    public User handle(UpdateUserInput updateUserInput) {\n    28→        final var user = findUserById.handle(updateUserInput.getId());\n    29→        checkValidations(updateUserInput, updateUserInput.getId());\n    30→        updateFields(user, updateUserInput);\n    31→        userRepository.update(modelValidator.validate(user));\n    32→        return user;\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→    private void updateFields(User user, UpdateUserInput updateUserInput) {\n    36→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getUsername())) {\n    37→            user.setUsername(updateUserInput.getUsername());\n    38→        }\n    39→\n    40→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getEmail())) {\n    41→            user.setEmail(updateUserInput.getEmail());\n    42→        }\n    43→\n    44→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getBio())) {\n    45→            user.setBio(updateUserInput.getBio());\n    46→        }\n    47→\n    48→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getImage())) {\n    49→            user.setImage(updateUserInput.getImage());\n    50→        }\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    private void checkValidations(UpdateUserInput updateUserInput, UUID excludeId) {\n    54→\n    55→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getUsername())) {\n    56→            checkUsername(excludeId, updateUserInput.getUsername());\n    57→        }\n    58→\n    59→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getEmail())) {\n    60→            checkEmail(excludeId, updateUserInput.getEmail());\n    61→        }\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    private boolean isPresent(String property) {\n    65→        return property != null && !property.isEmpty();\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    private void checkUsername(UUID selfId, String username) {\n    69→        if (userRepository.existsUsername(selfId, username)) {\n    70→            throw new UsernameAlreadyExistsException();\n    71→        }\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    private void checkEmail(UUID selfId, String email) {\n    75→        if (userRepository.existsEmail(selfId, email)) {\n    76→            throw new EmailAlreadyExistsException();\n    77→        }\n    78→    }\n    79→}\n    80→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VWywaoMKfDQLjyVUhPbx8t","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"4afa56ea-7b66-4e13-84e4-a474ac8fe63a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Fj9sksLuQbz4t4BVV1Aikx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature;\n     2→\n     3→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.NewArticleInput;\n     5→\n     6→public interface CreateArticle {\n     7→  Article handle(NewArticleInput newArticleInput);\n     8→}\n     9→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VWywaoMKfDQLjyVUhPbx8t","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"00feb50b-f08b-467f-b99b-013e324cf0e7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EcDqezY1g1ZJJQ8qEuDRa1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateArticle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateSlugByTitle;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.*;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    11→\n    12→import java.util.List;\n    13→\n    14→@Singleton\n    15→public class CreateArticleImpl implements CreateArticle {\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private CreateSlugByTitle createSlugByTitle;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists findTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    private TagRelationshipRepository tagRelationshipRepository;\n    29→\n    30→    @Override\n    31→    public Article handle(NewArticleInput newArticleInput) {\n    32→        final var author = findUserById.handle(newArticleInput.getAuthorId());\n    33→        final var slug = createSlugByTitle.handle(newArticleInput.getTitle());\n    34→        final var article =\n    35→                articleBuilder.build(\n    36→                        slug,\n    37→                        newArticleInput.getTitle(),\n    38→                        newArticleInput.getDescription(),\n    39→                        newArticleInput.getBody(),\n    40→                        author);\n    41→        articleRepository.save(article);\n    42→        List<String> tagList = newArticleInput.getTagList();\n    43→        if (tagList != null && !tagList.isEmpty()) {\n    44→            final List<Tag> tags = findTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists.handle(newArticleInput.getTagList());\n    45→            createTagRelationship(article, tags);\n    46→        }\n    47→        return article;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    private void createTagRelationship(Article article, List<Tag> tags) {\n    51→        tags.forEach(tag -> tagRelationshipRepository.save(new TagRelationship(article, tag)));\n    52→    }\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VWywaoMKfDQLjyVUhPbx8t","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"f0f6ccca-3dfc-40df-9acb-55430fde21e9"}
