{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XdpqQVL1HfvSmMMJvrKwwJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.ArticleNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindArticleByAuthorAndSlugImpl implements FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Article handle(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    20→        return articleRepository\n    21→                .findByAuthorAndSlug(authorId, slug)\n    22→                .orElseThrow(ArticleNotFoundException::new);\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017NwEeaDjxHWLLy7xd7fwK3","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"97b1a434-3e3d-433b-9627-17188312a891"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GSZa8tDbRKTePmSgV9H85X","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FavoriteArticle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    11→\n    12→import java.util.UUID;\n    13→\n    14→@Singleton\n    15→public class FavoriteArticleImpl implements FavoriteArticle {\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    23→\n    24→    @Override\n    25→    public FavoriteRelationship handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    26→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    27→        final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    28→                favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    29→        return favoriteRelationshipOptional.orElseGet(() -> createFavoriteRelationship(currentUserId, article));\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    private FavoriteRelationship createFavoriteRelationship(UUID currentUserId, Article article) {\n    33→        final var user = findUserById.handle(currentUserId);\n    34→        final var favoriteRelationship = new FavoriteRelationship(user, article);\n    35→        favoriteRelationshipRepository.save(favoriteRelationship);\n    36→        return favoriteRelationship;\n    37→    }\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017NwEeaDjxHWLLy7xd7fwK3","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"2aaa39c2-9695-43d6-a0cb-1577f12593ff"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F11kvNZUwpU38cE8bBk99c","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.DeleteComment;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\n     9→\n    10→@Singleton\n    11→public class DeleteCommentImpl implements DeleteComment {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private FindCommentByIdAndAuthor findCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public void handle(DeleteCommentInput deleteCommentInput) {\n    20→        final var comment =\n    21→                findCommentByIdAndAuthor.handle(\n    22→                        deleteCommentInput.getCommentId(), deleteCommentInput.getAuthorId());\n    23→        commentRepository.delete(comment);\n    24→    }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017NwEeaDjxHWLLy7xd7fwK3","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"64942cfe-f597-4537-9485-c5b82b40f554"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012wLHJvJoKPG31uDYSy1Jmn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.DeleteArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationshipRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.List;\n    15→import java.util.Optional;\n    16→import java.util.UUID;\n    17→\n    18→@Singleton\n    19→public class DeleteArticleBySlugImpl implements DeleteArticleBySlug {\n    20→\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug findArticleByAuthorAndSlug;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private TagRelationshipRepository tagRelationshipRepository;\n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    31→\n    32→    @Override\n    33→    public void handle(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    34→        final var article = findArticleByAuthorAndSlug.handle(authorId, slug);\n    35→        tagRelationshipRepository.delete(article);\n    36→        Optional<FavoriteRelationship> favorite = favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), authorId);\n    37→        favorite.ifPresent(favoriteRelationship -> favoriteRelationshipRepository.delete(favoriteRelationship));\n    38→        List<Comment> comments = commentRepository.findCommentsByArticle(article);\n    39→        comments.forEach(c -> commentRepository.delete(c));\n    40→        articleRepository.delete(article);\n    41→    }\n    42→}\n    43→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017NwEeaDjxHWLLy7xd7fwK3","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"7412467e-760d-4be6-96a4-fa7137025744"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016DDFnhRT3zZse7ywr3KCMC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.EmailAlreadyExistsException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UsernameAlreadyExistsException;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateUser;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.CreateUserInput;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    13→\n    14→@Singleton\n    15→public class CreateUserImpl implements CreateUser {\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private HashProvider hashProvider;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    23→\n    24→    @Override\n    25→    public User handle(CreateUserInput createUserInput) {\n    26→        final var user =\n    27→                userBuilder.build(\n    28→                        createUserInput.getUsername(),\n    29→                        createUserInput.getEmail(),\n    30→                        createUserInput.getPassword());\n    31→        checkExistingUsername(user.getUsername());\n    32→        checkExistingEmail(user.getEmail());\n    33→        user.setPassword(hashProvider.hashPassword(user.getPassword()));\n    34→        userRepository.save(user);\n    35→        return user;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    private void checkExistingUsername(String username) {\n    39→        if (userRepository.existsByUsername(username)) {\n    40→            throw new UsernameAlreadyExistsException();\n    41→        }\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    private void checkExistingEmail(String email) {\n    45→        if (userRepository.existsByEmail(email)) {\n    46→            throw new EmailAlreadyExistsException();\n    47→        }\n    48→    }\n    49→}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017NwEeaDjxHWLLy7xd7fwK3","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"bc91e2ce-db4b-40d4-83f2-a5d10b49f0b9"}
