{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016nmeh5QR3bfdkrcBBpjpWF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.LoginUserInput;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    12→\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class LoginUserImpl implements LoginUser {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    private HashProvider hashProvider;\n    20→\n    21→    @Override\n    22→    public User handle(LoginUserInput loginUserInput) {\n    23→        final var user =\n    24→                userRepository\n    25→                        .findByEmail(loginUserInput.getEmail())\n    26→                        .orElseThrow(UserNotFoundException::new);\n    27→        if (!isPasswordValid(loginUserInput.getPassword(), user.getPassword())) {\n    28→            throw new InvalidPasswordException();\n    29→        }\n    30→        return user;\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    private boolean isPasswordValid(String password, String hashedPassword) {\n    34→        return hashProvider.checkPassword(password, hashedPassword);\n    35→    }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017NwEeaDjxHWLLy7xd7fwK3","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"b3694d30-b450-452e-8500-fc1281f7f8f6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RYpAHZvVeCb61nPvBpficT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n     9→\n    10→@Dependent\n    11→public class FindUserByUsernameImpl implements FindUserByUsername {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    15→\n    16→    @Override\n    17→    public User handle(String username) {\n    18→        return userRepository.findByUsername(username).orElseThrow(UserNotFoundException::new);\n    19→    }\n    20→}\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017NwEeaDjxHWLLy7xd7fwK3","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"4ef66597-f75c-4204-b8b0-87ea118363f4"}
