{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NAfrb7zbCzsoXpCyWm43Wc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.Data;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.LinkedList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→\n     8→import static java.util.Collections.singletonList;\n     9→\n    10→@Data\n    11→public class BusinessException extends RuntimeException {\n    12→\n    13→  private final int code;\n    14→  private final List<String> messages;\n    15→\n    16→  public BusinessException(int code, String message) {\n    17→    super(message);\n    18→    this.code = code;\n    19→    this.messages = new LinkedList<>(singletonList(message));\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  public BusinessException(int code, List<String> messages) {\n    23→    super(String.join(\", \", messages));\n    24→    this.code = code;\n    25→    this.messages = messages;\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"5138cdac-afdf-40d8-bb9b-abd21881eeb1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SuU9a1Qvfz72qPJTAqFmVL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import lombok.Getter;\n     5→import lombok.Setter;\n     6→\n     7→import java.util.LinkedList;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→\n    10→@Getter\n    11→@Setter\n    12→@JsonRootName(\"errors\")\n    13→public class ErrorResponse {\n    14→\n    15→    private List<String> body;\n    16→\n    17→    public ErrorResponse() {\n    18→        this.body = new LinkedList<>();\n    19→    }\n    20→\n    21→    public ErrorResponse(String error) {\n    22→        this();\n    23→        this.body.add(error);\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    public ErrorResponse(List<String> errors) {\n    27→        this.body = errors;\n    28→    }\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"c7c87065-a0f1-4b33-a004-b4166dc73ca2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UmCDALbx9tPoQnobB4inPo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server description=\"Realworld Liberty server\">\n     2→    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_HOSTNAME\" defaultValue=\"localhost\"/>\n     3→    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_PORT\" defaultValue=\"5432\"/>\n     4→    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_DBNAME\" defaultValue=\"postgres_db\"/>\n     5→    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_USER\" defaultValue=\"postgres_user\"/>\n     6→    <variable name=\"POSTGRESQL_PW\" defaultValue=\"S3cret\"/>\n     7→\n     8→    <featureManager>\n     9→        <feature>beanValidation-3.0</feature>\n    10→        <feature>jsonb-3.0</feature>\n    11→        <feature>persistence-3.1</feature>\n    12→        <feature>restfulWS-3.1</feature>\n    13→        <feature>jdbc-4.3</feature>\n    14→        <feature>mpJwt-2.1</feature>\n    15→        <feature>mpConfig-3.0</feature>\n    16→        <feature>mpHealth-4.0</feature>\n    17→    </featureManager>\n    18→\n    19→    <httpEndpoint httpPort=\"8080\" httpsPort=\"9443\"\n    20→                  id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\"/>\n    21→\n    22→    <webApplication contextRoot=\"/\" location=\"realworld-liberty.war\"/>\n    23→\n    24→    <library id=\"postgresqlLib\">\n    25→        <fileset dir=\"jdbc\" includes=\"postgresql*.jar\"/>\n    26→    </library>\n    27→\n    28→    <dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/RealWorldSource\">\n    29→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"postgresqlLib\"/>\n    30→        <properties.postgresql serverName=\"${POSTGRESQL_HOSTNAME}\" portNumber=\"${POSTGRESQL_PORT}\"\n    31→                               databaseName=\"${POSTGRESQL_DBNAME}\" user=\"${POSTGRESQL_USER}\"\n    32→                               password=\"${POSTGRESQL_PW}\"/>\n    33→    </dataSource>\n    34→\n    35→    <cors domain=\"/api\"\n    36→          allowedOrigins=\"*\"\n    37→          allowedMethods=\"GET, POST, PUT\"\n    38→          allowedHeaders=\"*\"\n    39→          allowCredentials=\"true\"\n    40→          maxAge=\"3600\"/>\n    41→\n    42→    <mpJwt id=\"jwtHandler\" issuer=\"users-service\" authorizationHeaderScheme=\"Token \"/>\n    43→</server>\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"c7deb2be-5b76-4aa5-8e19-8e875ff29357"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Vi5bJtJBn8NQEh1MzobFVi","type":"tool_result","content":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_1/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/beans.xml\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_1/output/src/test/resources/META-INF/beans.xml"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"c5187c8c-ef0c-4535-8432-3cc92ae0e0c7"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CfgHyNT2YYZqqZBY1uu4AF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me now proceed with the migration. I'll set a working directory variable and start making all the changes. The key points for the migration are:\n\n1. **pom.xml**: Replace MicroProfile/Liberty with Quarkus BOM, change packaging from `war` to `jar`\n2. **Configuration**: Replace `persistence.xml` + `server.xml` + `microprofile-config.properties` with Quarkus `application.properties`\n3. **JPA**: Switch from `@PersistenceContext` EntityManager to `@Inject` with Quarkus Hibernate ORM\n4. **Security**: The JAX-RS filters work in Quarkus RESTEasy too, so keep them mostly the same\n5. **CDI**: Jakarta CDI annotations work in Quarkus, minimal changes needed\n6. **Build**: Use Quarkus Maven plugin instead of Liberty Maven plugin\n7. **Dockerfile**: Build a Quarkus app jar and run it\n\nLet me start writing all the files:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2432,"cache_read_input_tokens":108717,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2432,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2035},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"c7444397-3a76-4cc9-86d4-378fe0afa632"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CfgHyNT2YYZqqZBY1uu4AF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01TNJhRdV4v18uFbFDm1DB8j","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_1/output/pom.xml","content":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n\n    <groupId>projects</groupId>\n    <artifactId>realworld-quarkus</artifactId>\n    <version>1.0.0</version>\n    <packaging>jar</packaging>\n\n    <properties>\n        <maven.compiler.target>21</maven.compiler.target>\n        <maven.compiler.source>21</maven.compiler.source>\n        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n        <quarkus.platform.version>3.17.8</quarkus.platform.version>\n        <lombok.version>1.18.38</lombok.version>\n    </properties>\n\n    <dependencyManagement>\n        <dependencies>\n            <dependency>\n                <groupId>io.quarkus.platform</groupId>\n                <artifactId>quarkus-bom</artifactId>\n                <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n                <type>pom</type>\n                <scope>import</scope>\n            </dependency>\n        </dependencies>\n    </dependencyManagement>\n\n    <dependencies>\n        <!-- Quarkus core -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n            <artifactId>quarkus-arc</artifactId>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- RESTEasy Reactive with Jackson -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n            <artifactId>quarkus-resteasy-jackson</artifactId>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- Hibernate ORM with Panache -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n            <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-orm</artifactId>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- Hibernate Validator -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n            <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-validator</artifactId>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- PostgreSQL JDBC driver -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n            <artifactId>quarkus-jdbc-postgresql</artifactId>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- Quarkus Narayana JTA (transactions) -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n            <artifactId>quarkus-narayana-jta</artifactId>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- JWT (auth0 java-jwt) -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>com.auth0</groupId>\n            <artifactId>java-jwt</artifactId>\n            <version>4.5.0</version>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- BCrypt -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>at.favre.lib</groupId>\n            <artifactId>bcrypt</artifactId>\n            <version>0.10.2</version>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- Slugify -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>com.github.slugify</groupId>\n            <artifactId>slugify</artifactId>\n            <version>3.0.7</version>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- Jackson Java Time support -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype</groupId>\n            <artifactId>jackson-datatype-jsr310</artifactId>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- Apache Commons Lang -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>\n            <artifactId>commons-lang3</artifactId>\n            <version>3.18.0</version>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- Lombok -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>\n            <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>\n            <version>${lombok.version}</version>\n            <scope>provided</scope>\n        </dependency>\n\n        <!-- Test dependencies -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n            <artifactId>quarkus-junit5</artifactId>\n            <scope>test</scope>\n        </dependency>\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.rest-assured</groupId>\n            <artifactId>rest-assured</artifactId>\n            <scope>test</scope>\n        </dependency>\n    </dependencies>\n\n    <build>\n        <finalName>${project.artifactId}</finalName>\n        <plugins>\n            <plugin>\n                <groupId>io.quarkus.platform</groupId>\n                <artifactId>quarkus-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n                <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n                <extensions>true</extensions>\n                <executions>\n                    <execution>\n                        <goals>\n                            <goal>build</goal>\n                            <goal>generate-code</goal>\n                            <goal>generate-code-tests</goal>\n                        </goals>\n                    </execution>\n                </executions>\n            </plugin>\n            <plugin>\n                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n                <version>3.13.0</version>\n                <configuration>\n                    <source>21</source>\n                    <target>21</target>\n                    <annotationProcessorPaths>\n                        <path>\n                            <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>\n                            <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>\n                            <version>${lombok.version}</version>\n                        </path>\n                    </annotationProcessorPaths>\n                </configuration>\n            </plugin>\n            <plugin>\n                <groupId>o