{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C2FcuordQB5oQFzjgznG5N","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable;\n     4→import lombok.Getter;\n     5→import lombok.Setter;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.NewArticleInput;\n     7→\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Getter\n    12→@Setter\n    13→public class NewArticleRequest {\n    14→\n    15→    private String title;\n    16→    private String description;\n    17→    private String body;\n    18→    private List<String> tagList;\n    19→\n    20→    public NewArticleInput toNewArticleInput(UUID loggedUserId) {\n    21→        return new NewArticleInput(loggedUserId, this.title, this.description, this.body, this.tagList);\n    22→    }\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Kb8sWbiuNTgLv8MJ85fnZV","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"da69d673-d062-4bad-bb15-ed77d3e280c7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012YradjVmm1R7m6bLVfUzfH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbNillable;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     5→import lombok.Getter;\n     6→import lombok.Setter;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.NewCommentInput;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Getter\n    13→@Setter\n    14→public class NewCommentRequest {\n    15→    @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    16→    private String body;\n    17→\n    18→    public NewCommentInput toNewCommentInput(UUID authorId, String articleSlug) {\n    19→        return new NewCommentInput(authorId, articleSlug, this.body);\n    20→    }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Kb8sWbiuNTgLv8MJ85fnZV","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"9744f46e-4543-4b45-8f32-5013e60df740"}
