{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0131P844PjuHMmjCZQfecGys","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n     7→\n     8→import java.util.UUID;\n     9→\n    10→@Singleton\n    11→@Named(\"usermodelbuilder\")\n    12→public class UserModelBuilder {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    16→\n    17→    public User build(String username, String email, String password) {\n    18→        return modelValidator.validate(\n    19→                new User(UUID.randomUUID(), username, email, password, null, null));\n    20→    }\n    21→\n    22→    public User build(\n    23→            UUID id, String username, String bio, String image, String password, String email) {\n    24→        return modelValidator.validate(new User(id, username, email, password, bio, image));\n    25→    }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"8f2af317-e02c-4c4c-832e-87f46ad90626"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DxGjPDh2Uw9ooNd4wmJTcY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n     7→\n     8→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class ArticleModelBuilder {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    16→\n    17→    public Article build(String slug, String title, String description, String body, User author) {\n    18→        final var createdAt = LocalDateTime.now();\n    19→        return modelValidator.validate(\n    20→                new Article(\n    21→                        UUID.randomUUID(), slug, title, description, body, createdAt, createdAt, author));\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    public Article build(\n    25→            UUID id,\n    26→            String slug,\n    27→            String title,\n    28→            String description,\n    29→            String body,\n    30→            LocalDateTime createdAt,\n    31→            LocalDateTime updatedAt,\n    32→            User author) {\n    33→        return modelValidator.validate(\n    34→                new Article(id, slug, title, description, body, createdAt, updatedAt, author));\n    35→    }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":