{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GVXtgcWQVPu25PiUpdQ3xE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import lombok.Getter;\n     5→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     6→import lombok.Setter;\n     7→\n     8→import java.util.Objects;\n     9→\n    10→@Getter\n    11→@Setter\n    12→@Entity\n    13→@NoArgsConstructor\n    14→@Table(name = \"FOLLOW_RELATIONSHIP\")\n    15→@NamedQueries({\n    16→        @NamedQuery(name = \"FREisFollowing\", query = \"select f from FollowRelationshipEntity f where f.user.id = :currentUserId and f.followed.id = :followedUserId\"),\n    17→        @NamedQuery(name = \"FRE.findByPrimaryKey_UserAndPrimaryKey_Followed\", query = \"select f from FollowRelationshipEntity f where f.user = :loggedUserEntity and f.followed = :followedUserEntity\")\n    18→})\n    19→public class FollowRelationshipEntity {\n    20→\n    21→    @Id\n    22→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)\n    23→    private Long id;\n    24→\n    25→    @ManyToOne\n    26→    @JoinColumn(updatable = false)\n    27→    private UserEntity user;\n    28→\n    29→    @ManyToOne\n    30→    @JoinColumn(updatable = false)\n    31→    private UserEntity followed;\n    32→\n    33→    public FollowRelationshipEntity(UserEntity user, UserEntity followed) {\n    34→        this.followed = followed;\n    35→        this.user = user;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    @Override\n    39→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    40→        if (this == o) return true;\n    41→\n    42→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    43→\n    44→        FollowRelationshipEntity that = (FollowRelationshipEntity) o;\n    45→        return Objects.equals(user, that.user) && Objects.equals(followed, that.followed);\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    @Override\n    49→    public int hashCode() {\n    50→        return Objects.hash(user, followed);\n    51→    }\n    52→}\n    53→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LzZGPxCtu5446xaNVZM4uz","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"1a4ae223-54cf-4f84-a7f3-c32fe03aaa69"}
