{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LzfNs8TJkXWMfkbxCE18Fo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\n     6→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class SerializerConfig {\n    14→\n    15→    @Singleton\n    16→    @Produces\n    17→    public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n    18→        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    19→        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    20→        objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    21→        objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    22→        return objectMapper;\n    23→    }\n    24→\n    25→    @Singleton\n    26→    @Produces\n    27→    @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper\n    28→    public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n    29→        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"0f507f5c-6bdd-4dd3-a54e-b7e5a93c5492"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014ALvmihxaJrRnfNAX5njkW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n     4→\n     5→import java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\n     6→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n     7→import java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\n     8→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n     9→\n    10→@Qualifier\n    11→@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n    12→@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.FIELD, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.PARAMETER})\n    13→public @interface NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper {\n    14→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"e7930b6d-916e-4acf-900b-2ffa2b3bec5d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bt1gdEQiaofuYqNQuPcduL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import lombok.Getter;\n     5→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     6→import lombok.Setter;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     8→\n     9→@Getter\n    10→@Setter\n    11→@NoArgsConstructor\n    12→@JsonRootName(\"user\")\n    13→public class UserResponse {\n    14→\n    15→    private String username;\n    16→    private String bio;\n    17→    private String image;\n    18→    private String email;\n    19→    private String token;\n    20→\n    21→    public UserResponse(User user, String token) {\n    22→        this.username = user.getUsername();\n    23→        this.bio = user.getBio();\n    24→        this.image = user.getImage();\n    25→        this.email = user.getEmail();\n    26→        this.token = token;\n    27→    }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"cb73a8aa-3307-439c-a5bb-8361c8b927c8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ErdT2s5qXEEhqDjTku2v46","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleModelBuilder;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationship;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class EntityUtils {\n    19→\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    @Named(\"usermodelbuilder\")\n    22→    private UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    private CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    29→\n    30→    public User user(UserEntity userEntity) {\n    31→        final var id = userEntity.getId();\n    32→        final var username = userEntity.getUsername();\n    33→        final var bio = userEntity.getBio();\n    34→        final var image = userEntity.getImage();\n    35→        final var password = userEntity.getPassword();\n    36→        final var email = userEntity.getEmail();\n    37→        return userBuilder.build(id, username, bio, image, password, email);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public Tag tag(TagEntity tagEntity) {\n    41→        return tagBuilder.build(tagEntity.getId(), tagEntity.getName());\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    public Tag tag(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    45→        return tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getTag());\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public TagRelationship tagRelationship(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    49→        return new TagRelationship(article(tagRelationshipEntity.getArticle()), tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getTag()));\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    public Article article(ArticleEntity articleEntity) {\n    53→        return articleBuilder.build(\n    54→                articleEntity.getId(),\n    55→                articleEntity.getSlug(),\n    56→                articleEntity.getTitle(),\n    57→                articleEntity.getDescription(),\n    58→                articleEntity.getBody(),\n    59→                articleEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    60→                articleEntity.getUpdatedAt(),\n    61→                user(articleEntity.getAuthor()));\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    public Comment comment(CommentEntity commentEntity) {\n    65→        return commentBuilder.build(\n    66→                commentEntity.getId(),\n    67→                user(commentEntity.getAuthor()),\n    68→                article(commentEntity.getArticle()),\n    69→                commentEntity.getBody(),\n    70→                commentEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    71→                commentEntity.getUpdatedAt());\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    public FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship(\n    75→            FavoriteRelationshipEntity favoriteRelationshipEntity) {\n    76→        return new FavoriteRelationship(\n    77→                user(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getUser()),\n    78→                article(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getArticle()));\n    79→    }\n    80→}\n    81→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"ceb68101-691b-40a8-a2b0-d4d63e6082ea"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01KtwBawwwmVoYtUDj1eoHL7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see a critical issue with `SerializerConfig.java` - it produces a custom `ObjectMapper` bean with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled. In Quarkus, the default `ObjectMapper` is managed by Quarkus (quarkus-jackson), and having a custom CDI producer might conflict. However, the approach used here (producing `ObjectMapper` via CDI `@Produces`) should work with Quarkus since we're using `quarkus-resteasy-jackson`.\n\nBut there's a bigger concern: Quarkus might register its own default `ObjectMapper`, which would conflict with this custom one. Let me also check the `@ConfigProperty` import in JwtTokenProvider - Quarkus ships MicroProfile Config so `org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty` should work. Let me verify the remaining critical files:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3167,"cache_read_input_tokens":46856,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3167,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":638},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"4cfcc0e4-737e-4efd-81b1-de93ae5d79b8"}
