{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01A7dR5Np8BLJmworwayXuZ4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I need to handle a potential ObjectMapper conflict in Quarkus. When `quarkus-resteasy-jackson` is used, Quarkus manages its own ObjectMapper. Our custom producer may conflict. The proper Quarkus way is to use `ObjectMapperCustomizer`. However, since we need two different ObjectMapper instances (one with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE and one without), and the code injects them directly, we can keep the CDI producer approach but need to make sure Quarkus doesn't also try to produce one. Let me check if there's an issue by adding a Quarkus-compatible approach:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1498,"cache_read_input_tokens":59798,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1498,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":377},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"e1cd37b6-42b9-4ea5-8008-36229d898d39"}
