{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PzTMuVo1yQVqwTVw8TeNJ9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import lombok.Getter;\n     7→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     8→import lombok.Setter;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    10→\n    11→@Getter\n    12→@Setter\n    13→@AllArgsConstructor\n    14→@NoArgsConstructor\n    15→public class NewUserRequestWrapper {\n    16→\n    17→    @Valid\n    18→    @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    19→    private NewUserRequest user;\n    20→\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"ed00bd59-4257-4495-a2cb-1d0eee8f3566"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01912X4Zq5RwyzXk6mv6yj8H","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.Getter;\n     4→import lombok.Setter;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     6→\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     9→\n    10→@Getter\n    11→@Setter\n    12→public class TagsResponse {\n    13→\n    14→    private List<String> tags;\n    15→\n    16→    public TagsResponse(List<Tag> tags) {\n    17→        this.tags = tags.stream().map(Tag::getName).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    18→    }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"a4f62db4-e24e-40ae-b3c4-0b5b2dd4dbb1"}
