{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014TQkgPjCzGbmkYJDvjWt5m","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Migration Complete\n\nThe Jakarta EE (Open Liberty) to Quarkus migration is finished. Here's the summary:\n\n### Results\n- **72/72 smoke tests passed** - all API endpoints working correctly\n- Application starts on Quarkus 3.17.8 in ~3.8 seconds\n\n### Key Changes Made\n1. **pom.xml**: Replaced Liberty/MicroProfile dependencies with Quarkus BOM 3.17.8, changed packaging from WAR to JAR\n2. **application.properties**: New consolidated config replacing `persistence.xml`, `server.xml`, `microprofile-config.properties`\n3. **JPA**: Changed `@PersistenceContext` to `@Inject` for EntityManager, rewrote DAOs with proper CDI scopes\n4. **Entity layer**: Simplified relationship entity IDs from composite keys to auto-generated `Long` IDs\n5. **Serialization**: Created `@WrapRootValueObjectMapper` qualifier to separate the WRAP_ROOT_VALUE ObjectMapper from Quarkus's default (used by RESTEasy for request deserialization)\n6. **Bug fix**: Removed invalid `@Context SecurityException` parameter from `UsersResource.create()`\n7. **Deleted**: Liberty-specific files (`server.xml`, `persistence.xml`, `beans.xml`, old tests)\n8. **start.sh/Dockerfile**: Updated for Quarkus jar runner (`quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar`)\n\n### Error Encountered and Resolved\nThe initial build started successfully but smoke tests failed because the `ObjectMapperCustomizer` applied `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE`/`UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` to the global RESTEasy ObjectMapper, breaking request deserialization and wrapping all responses with class names. Fixed by using qualified CDI beans for the WRAP_ROOT_VALUE ObjectMapper."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":690,"cache_read_input_tokens":130697,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":690,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":437},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","uuid":"ee6f485d-46d3-4310-98db-03c84d27e126"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":2409748,"duration_api_ms":3362348,"num_turns":197,"result":"## Migration Complete\n\nThe Jakarta EE (Open Liberty) to Quarkus migration is finished. Here's the summary:\n\n### Results\n- **72/72 smoke tests passed** - all API endpoints working correctly\n- Application starts on Quarkus 3.17.8 in ~3.8 seconds\n\n### Key Changes Made\n1. **pom.xml**: Replaced Liberty/MicroProfile dependencies with Quarkus BOM 3.17.8, changed packaging from WAR to JAR\n2. **application.properties**: New consolidated config replacing `persistence.xml`, `server.xml`, `microprofile-config.properties`\n3. **JPA**: Changed `@PersistenceContext` to `@Inject` for EntityManager, rewrote DAOs with proper CDI scopes\n4. **Entity layer**: Simplified relationship entity IDs from composite keys to auto-generated `Long` IDs\n5. **Serialization**: Created `@WrapRootValueObjectMapper` qualifier to separate the WRAP_ROOT_VALUE ObjectMapper from Quarkus's default (used by RESTEasy for request deserialization)\n6. **Bug fix**: Removed invalid `@Context SecurityException` parameter from `UsersResource.create()`\n7. **Deleted**: Liberty-specific files (`server.xml`, `persistence.xml`, `beans.xml`, old tests)\n8. **start.sh/Dockerfile**: Updated for Quarkus jar runner (`quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar`)\n\n### Error Encountered and Resolved\nThe initial build started successfully but smoke tests failed because the `ObjectMapperCustomizer` applied `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE`/`UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` to the global RESTEasy ObjectMapper, breaking request deserialization and wrapping all responses with class names. Fixed by using qualified CDI beans for the WRAP_ROOT_VALUE ObjectMapper.","session_id":"d54d9ac2-22a6-4fd0-85db-0f21ac49e7c7","total_cost_usd":29.10007605999997,"usage":{"input_tokens":154,"cache_creation_input_tokens":402905,"cache_read_input_tokens":6479515,"output_tokens":55309,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"serv